==English==

===Pronunciation===
UK: ro?ot, sometimes in the US: rout
*{{audio|en-uk-route.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
====Homophones====
*[[root]] ''(In some dialects)''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The course or way which is traveled or passed, or is to be passed.
# A passing; a course; a road or path; a march.

====Translations====
*French: [[chemin]] {{m}} (1), [[route]] {{m}} (1, 2)
*Japanese: [[通路]](つうろ, tūro) (1), [[路線]](ろせん, rosen) (2)

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|rout|e}}

# To direct or divert along a particular course.
#: The '''route''' was used so much that it formed a [[rut]].

===Anagrams===
*[[outer]]

